1. **Protagonist**: A night watchman named Kael, who patrols a city where time moves backward;  
2. **Dilemma**: He must decide whether to stop a man from walking into a building that will explode—knowing it will erase his own existence;  
3. **Decision**: He lets the man pass, whispering, “You’re not late.”;  
4. **Climax**: The explosion happens—but in reverse, the building reassembles, and Kael fades from memory;  
5. **Outcome**: The city is saved—but no one remembers him;  
6. **Clever Twist**: Kael was the explosion—his death created the loop;  
7. **Clever Worldbuilding Feature**: In this city, every person’s life is a loop—until they choose to break it;  
8. **Scene**: The man walks in—*backwards*—;  
9. **Punctuation**: “You’re not supposed to be here,” Kael said.  
10. **Punctuation**: The man smiled—;  
11. **Punctuation**: “I know.”  
12. **Punctuation**: The building cracked—;  
13. **Punctuation**: And then—;  
14. **Punctuation**: It rebuilt itself—;  
15. **Punctuation**: And Kael…  
16. **Punctuation**: …was gone.  
17. **Punctuation**: But the watchman’s log remained—;  
18. **Punctuation**: “I was here,” it read.  
19. **Punctuation**: “And I’m still watching.”  
20. **Punctuation**: “I always am.”?!  

